/p>
<p><strong>Step 1: Determine the start and end times</strong></p>
<p>Let=E2=80=99s say your start time is 9:30 AM and your end time is 2:15 P=
M.</p>
<p><strong>Step 2: Convert the time to a 24-hour (a.k.a. military time) for=
mat</strong></p>
<p>To do this, add 12 to the hours of any PM times, or use our <a class=3D"=
body-internal-link" href=3D"https://www.ontheclock.com/convert-military-24-=
hour-time.aspx">military time converter</a>. In this case, 9:30 AM would be=
come 0930, and 2:15 PM would become 1415.</p>
<p><strong>Step 3: Calculate the time difference</strong></p>
<p>Subtract the start hours from the end hours to calculate the time differ=
ence (e.g., 1400 - 900 =3D 500). Then, do the same with minutes (e.g., 15 -=
 30 =3D -15).</p>
<p><strong>Step 4: Handle any borrow or carry-over</strong></p>
</div>
