ge-pill">A</span></div>
<div class=3D"theAnswer">
<p>To calculate the duration of time in minutes, you need to consider the n=
umber of hours and minutes involved. To convert hours to minutes, multiply =
the number of hours by 60. Next, if you have any additional minutes beyond =
the whole hours, simply add them to the total.</p>
<p>So, for example, let=E2=80=99s say you=E2=80=99d like to convert 2 hours=
 and 30 minutes into minutes. First, you would multiply 2 by 60, resulting =
in 120 minutes. Then, you=E2=80=99d add the remaining 30 minutes. The resul=
t is 150 minutes because 120 + 30 =3D 150.</p>
</div>
